n little progress on inflation over the past year. The 12-month change in the headline personal consumption expenditures (PCE) price index for December 2025 was 2.9%, above its December 2024 value. The 12-month core PCE inflation rate, which excludes the volatile food and energy categories, was 3.0%, unchanged from its year-ago value. Inflation readings for 2025 were likely influenced by the imposition of new tariffs. [...] ## Strong January employment report stabilizes labor outlook\\\\n\\\\nDespite a robust January employment report which showed an increase in nonfarm payroll employment of 130,000 new jobs, prior jobs data show that that the labor market has cooled. Private-sector employment gains in January were particularly strong, adding 172,000 jobs. Federal government employment fell by 34,000 jobs, influenced by continued separations associated with deferred resignation programs that were initiated last year.\\\", \\\"score\\\": 0.036493763, \\\"raw_content\\\": null}], \\\"response_time\\\": 6.03, \\\"request_id\\\": \\\"21bf48fa-ff96-4ba9-a622-ee86ce6ef519\\\"}\", \"tool_name\": \"web_search\"}",
